<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>



<IMG SRC="images/folio1.gif" ALT="GreenBeat!"
ALIGN=top><BR> <P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2>Andrei Zot&#248;v Vladimirovich</FONT><BR> <FONT SIZE=+1>River Watch 
Foreign Exchange Student</FONT></CENTER><BR> <P> <IMG
SRC="images/russian.jpeg" ALIGN=LEFT ALT="Andre" WIDTH=103 HEIGHT=127
VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10><BR><FONT SIZE=+1> <B>Age:</B> 16<P> <B>From:</B>
Obnisk, Russia - 2 hours by train southwest of Moscow<BR></FONT><P>

<FONT SIZE=+3>A</FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>

ndrei Zot&#248;v is near the end of his 3-week tour of Central Texas.  On this night,
10 Russian students and their leader, Vadim Kalinin, have prepared a traditional
five-course Russian meal for their host families in Austin.  The students whirl
about the kitchen with great purpose and our GreenBeat reporter waits for Andrei
to finish his duties before he can step outside to discuss his involvement with
the Russian environmental program.

"Before the breakup of the Soviet Union," says Andrei, "my father was a
scientist.  I had alway thought I would be one as well. Now scientists make very
little money so my father has taken another job where he is only a manager.  This
change was very hard for my family, I lost sense of what I might do with my own
life."

<IMG SRC="images/soccer.gif" ALT="Andre A&A"
ALIGN=RIGHT VSPACE=6 HSPACE=6 WIDTH=286 HEIGHT=104>


I met Vadim while at Obninsk College (equivalent to a U.S. high school). He is
one of the first formal environmental teachers in all of Russia.  He started an
environmental club and I joined.  We have taken many trips and seen many
interesting things about the natural world.  This has given me a way of seeing
that is more (Andrei gestures in circles he searches for the English word),
Ecological."

"Now I plan to become an environmental scientist."  says Andrei.  "After college
I hope to attend the Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology."<P>



