<TITLE>Centre for Renewal in Public Policy</TITLE></HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">



<a href="http://www.rohmcom.com/bin/imagemap.cgi/crpphome">
<CENTER><IMG ALIGN="TOP" SRC="./gifs/home.jpg" ALT="Menu Bar" BORDER=0 ISMAP="ISMAP"></CENTER></a><br>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1>46E Sunac St.<br>Gloucester, Ontario, K1J 6P7<br>Phone:  (613) 567-9010  Fax:  567-6061<br>E-mail:  <a href="mailto:crpp@inasec.ca">crpp@inasec.ca</a></FONT>

<H1><HR SIZE=4>W E L C O M E</H2></CENTER>



<FONT SIZE=+1>The Centre for Renewal in Public Policy is an independent, non-profit,
charitable organization dedicated to addressing important, but often
over-looked, questions relevant to public policy formulation in Canada.  The Centre is committed 
to producing first class publications and hosting educational events that raise key questions
in a way that will be helpful for scholars, professionals, politicians, bureaucrats and citizens 
from all walks of life.  The Centre for Renewal in Public Policy is made up of leaders who, while they represent a
broad variety of political and religious affiliations, all share a belief in the importance of the Jewish and Christian traditions as living traditions.</FONT><BR><BR>
<CENTER>

