<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H4><I>Internetwork Analysis and Troubleshooting</I></H4>
Critical business functions in today's networks rely heavily on
internetworking technology. Client-server computing, access to Internet and
Intranet require a reliable and efficient network infrastructure. This
seminar examines LAN/WAN internetworking and network troubleshooting
techniques.<BR><BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B><FONT COLOR="F3C228"><FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>OPICS OF DISCUSSION INCLUDE:</FONT></B>

<UL TYPE=square>
<H5><LI><I>Overview of Networking Technologies</I>

<UL>
<LI>LAN
<LI>WAN
<LI>Routing/Switching
<LI>ATM
</UL>

<LI><I>Analysis and Troubleshooting Techniques</I>

<UL>
<LI>Protocol encapsulation and tunnelling
<LI>Protocol overhead analysis
<LI>Transit delay analysis
<LI>Baselining
<LI>Load simulation and generation
<LI>Identifying routing problems
<LI>Identifying other internetwork problems</H5>
</UL>

</UL>

<BR>
<B><FONT COLOR="F3C228"><FONT SIZE=+1>S</FONT>TEP BY STEP EXAMPLES OF:</FONT></B>

<H5><UL>
<LI>Frame capture and analysis
<LI>Traffic generation and filtering
<LI><A NAME="Locations"></A>How to use protocol analyzers
</UL></H5>
</BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>

<BR><BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
