<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>ATM Test Methodologies - Wandel & Goltermann</TITLE>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="author" CONTENT="Rohm Communications">
<META HTTP-EQUIV="description" CONTENT="ATM Test Methodologies Seminar by Wandel & Goltermann">
<META HTTP-EQUIV="keywords" CONTENT="ATM, NETWORK, WANDEL, GOLTERMANN,">
<META HTTP-EQUIV="distribution" CONTENT="global">
<META HTTP-EQUIV="resource-type" CONTENT="document">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFBB0F" LINK="#4D00CF" VLINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF0041"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0>
<TR><TD VALIGN=top>

<TABLE BORDER=3  CELLSPACING=6>
<TR><TD BGCOLOR="#FFCF53" ALIGN=center VALIGN=middle>
<H1><FONT SIZE=+6>ATM</FONT><BR>
T<FONT SIZE=+2>EST</FONT> M<FONT SIZE=+2>ETHODOLOGIES</FONT>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center VALIGN=top>
<B><FONT SIZE=+2>P</FONT>ERFORMANCE <FONT SIZE=+2>S</FONT>OLUTION <FONT SIZE=+2>S</FONT>EMINAR</B>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<BR><H2>by <A HREF="http://www.wgcanada.com"><B>Wandel & Goltermann</B></A></H2>
</CENTER><BR><BR>

<BLOCKQUOTE><B>ATM</B> (<I>Asynchronous Transfer Mode</I>) is rapidly emerging from the R&D lab to client production networks.  Along with <B>ATM</B>'s exciting new service opportunities come a whole new set of challenges in network deployment and maintenance.  This seminar will cover key <B>ATM</B> network testing issues and strategies which will help you verify and maintain the robust service levels your customers demand.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=6>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center>
<H3><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"><FONT SIZE=+2>T</FONT>OPICS <FONT SIZE=+2>T</FONT>O <FONT SIZE=+2>B</FONT>E <FONT SIZE=+2>C</FONT>OVERED</FONT><BR>
<HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=60%>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=top>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><H3>ATM Test Challenges
<LI><H3>How To Recognize Network Problems
<LI><H3>Quality Of Service: What Is It?
<LI><H3>Quality Of Service: How To Test For It
<LI><H3>ATM Traffic Contracts
<LI><H3>ATM Service Testing Methodology</H3>
</UL>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLSPACING=10>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center><B>City</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN=center><B>Date</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN=center><B>Time</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN=center><B>Location</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center>Montreal</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Mon. October 28</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>9:00-11:30</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Queen Elizabeth Hotel<BR>900 Rene Levesque</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center>Ottawa</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Tue. October 29</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>9:00-11:30</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Minto Suites Hotel<BR>433 Laurier W</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center>Toronto</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Wed. October 30</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>9:00-11:30</TD>
<TD ALIGN=center>Holiday Crowne Plaza<BR>225 Front Street W</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><H2><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">About The Speaker</FONT></H2>
<I>Edward Sztuka</I> is Vice President and co-founder of <I>DeskNet Systems</I>.  Mr. Sztuka has been involved in FDDI, ESCON, and <B>ATM</B> systems development programs for many years and has held engineering positions at leading data communications companies.  Mr. Sztuka has also been active in both the <B>ATM</B> Forum and ANSI X3T9.5 committee and has a BS in electrical engineering from the University of Bridgeport.<BR><BR><BR>

<H2><A HREF="http://www.wgcanada.com">Wandel & Goltermann</A></H2>
<I>Wandel & Goltermann</I> provides network performance, analysis and management solutions to leading companies around the world.  In Canada, <I>Wandel & Goltermann</I> offers <B>ATM</B> and other technology solutions from strategic vendors covering every need including R&D, commissioning and field service.  As <B>ATM</B> proliferates as a network protocol, <I>Wandel & Goltermann</I> will be there to provide you with the tools and expertise to achieve your goals.</BLOCKQUOTE>


