<HEAD>
<TITLE>How to Get Started...</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="./gifs/pbbckgnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P><BASEFONT SIZE="4">

</FONT></P>
<CENTER>
<H1><B>P.B. FRASER &amp; ASSOCIATES</B>
<BR><IMG SRC="./gifs/pbicon.gif" WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="46" ALIGN="left"><IMG
SRC="./gifs/pbicon.gif" WIDTH="51" HEIGHT="46" ALIGN="right">Financial
Strategies Group</H1>
<H3>Member of Canadian Association of Financial Planners
<BR>and Life Underwriters Association of Canada</H3>
<HR SIZE="4"> 
<H1>GETTING STARTED...</H1>
<P><BR>
</P>
<H3>For information call <I>(613) 722-6830</I> or Fax us at <I>(613) 722-2936</I>.</H3>
<H3></H3>
<P>824 Meath Street<BR> Ottawa, Ontario<BR> K1Z 6E8</P> 
<H2><A HREF="./directns.html"> Click here for driving <I>Directions</I></A></H2>
<HR SIZE="4"> </CENTER>
<P><BR></P>
<H2><I>Important Homework to bring along on your first<BR> visit to
P.B. Fraser &amp; Associates</I></H2>
<P><BR></P>
<P><UL>
<LI><B>Last two years' tax returns</B></LI></UL><UL>
<LI><B>Life insurance Policies</B></LI></UL><UL>
<LI><B>Group Benefits Information</B></LI></UL><UL>
<LI><B>Current statements for all investments</B></LI></UL><UL>
<LI><B>Current R.R.S.P. statements</B></LI></UL><UL>
<LI><B>List of all assets and debts</B></LI></UL> 
</P><BR>
<P><IMG SRC="./gifs/pbicon2.gif" WIDTH="41" HEIGHT="33" ALIGN="baseline">A
comprehensive written Personal Finance Strategy will be presented to you.  It
will include a fact finding interview, full disclosure and assessment of your
situation, analysis of your personal objectives and goals, and the establishment
and implementation of plan strategies.  These will be conveniently organized in
a binder with dividers for <I>P.B. Fraser &amp; Associates</I> statements and
other items.</P> 
<P>Your Personal Finance Strategy incorporates a three-step process:</P> 
<P><BR><B>Meeting 1</B> 
</P>
<P>An introductory evaluation and the full confidential disclosure of your own
personal situation.  From this, with your permission, a comprehensive financial
strategy will be constructed, using the latest, most competitive analytical data
available today.</P> 
<P><BR><B>Meeting 2</B> 
</P>
<P>The presentation by a licensed qualified practitioner of the written
strategies developed specifically for you.  At this point the most important
elements of teaching and guiding take place.</P> 
<P><BR><B>Meeting 3</B> 
</P>
<P>The deployment and implementation of the strategies presented in meeting 2. 
Your pace and comfort determines the speed at which this takes place and it is
our pleasure to be available as often and as many times as it takes for you.</P>
<P>In addition, we communicate with you throughout the year in the following
ways:</P> 
<TABLE BORDER="2" CELLPADDING="2" CELLSPACING="2">
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">
<B>Investment statements:
</B></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>
January/April/July/October
</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1">
<B>Teleconferences on selected topics of interest:
</B></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>Bimonthly
</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1"><B>Updates of your personal finance strategies:
</B></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>1-4 times/year
</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1"><B>P.B. Fraser &amp; Associates Learning Conference:
</B></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>Annually
</B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSTART="1"><B>&quot;Thinking Outside the Box&quot; Newsletter:
</B></TD><TD COLSTART="2"><B>Quarterly
</B></TD></TR>
 
</TABLE>
<P>Our one-time planning fee will be cheerfully returned if you are not
completely satisfied!</P> 
