<CENTER>
<H1>R E S O U R C E S</H1>

<H2>BUILDING YOUR OWN LIBRARY</H2></CENTER>



<P>Our newsletter,  <A HREF="./news.html">Centrepoints</A>,  includes reviews of both newly

published and previously published books that speak to the issues that the

Centre is concerned with.  Reviewed books are available for order

through the Centre, as are tapes of the Centre's most recent lectures and

forums.</P>



<P>Prices are listed for each item to help

cover the cost of the product, and the shipping and handling.  Cheques, money

orders or Visa may be used for payment. Currently, we do not offer direct online purchasing, but if

you use our <A HREF="q&a.html">Q & A</A> page, you may indicate which

items you are interested in and we will contact you to arrange payment.</P>



<P><B>Tapes and Books Presently Available</B></P>



<P><I>Taped Lectures:</I></P>



<UL>

<LI>Public Leadership - Private Belief - Ian Shugart, Executive Director of

the Medical Research Council of Canada, examines the role of private belief and conviction in the exercise

of public leadership. - $10.00.<BR>

<LI>The Myth of Moral Neutrality - Dr. John Patrick, Pediatrician and

Professor of Biochemistry at the University of Ottawa, examines the

necessity of objective moral truth. - $10.00.

</UL>



<P><I>Books  (see reviews for description):</I></P>



<UL>

<LI><A HREF="./nws134.html"> Bankrupt Education: The Decline of Liberal Education in Canada</A> - Emberley, P.C. and Newell, W.R. (1994) - $TBA

<LI><A HREF="./nws123.html"> The Demoralization of Society</A> - by Gertrude Himmelfarb. - $34.00.<BR>

<LI><A HREF="./nws123.html#Noll">The Scandal of the Evangelical Mind</A> - by Mark A. Noll. - $28.00.

</UL>


