<H2>About the Author</H2>

<P>M.H. Ogilvie is Professor of Law at Carleton Uni-versity,
Ottawa. Educated at Trinity College, University of Toronto, the University
of Oxford and the Faculty of Law at Dalhousie University, and a member of
the Bars of Ontario and Nova Scotia.  Dr. Ogilvie has taught at Carleton
since 1978 and has been a visiting professor at the Universities of
Edinburgh, Toronto and Oxford.  Elected a Fellow of the Royal Society of
Canada in 1993, she is the author or editor of numerous books and articles,
primarily on Contract Law, Banking Law, Commercial Law, and Law and
Religion. She has a book coming out in Autumn 1996 (Carswell) on
religious-institutions law in Canada; it is intended for church
administrators as well as for lawyers.<BR>

