<HEAD>
<TITLE>Allan D. Weiss in Detail...</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="./gifs/pbbckgnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>

<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=10>
<TR><TD ALIGN=middle>

<H2><I>Allan D. Weiss</I><BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="./gifs/allan.gif" ALT="Picture of Allan Weiss" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=200 HSPACE=0 ALIGN=top><BR><BR>
<I>Financial Planner</I><BR>
<H3><P>"Consumers in the 90's are realizing the importance of getting back to fundamentals:  covering your risks;  saving for the future;  investing for growth but with a healthy respect for balance, diversification and quality;  and knowing when to get help from a qualified professional."
</TD><TD ROWSPAN=5 VALIGN=top>
<H3>
<P><IMG SRC="gifs/pbicon2.gif" WIDTH=41 HEIGHT=33 ALIGN=baseline>Allan Weiss received his Bachelor of Science degree from McGill University in Montreal, in 1969.  After seven years as a medical laboratory technologist, he entered the trust industry, moving to Ottawa in 1978.  In his time in that sector, he held positions as a trust manager, trust officer and account manager.  In 1992, Allan decided to use his experience in estate and trust administration, tax preparation, and portfolio trading to serve his clients directly, by becoming an independent financial planner.  Allan is a member of the Canadian Association of Financial Planners, and is continually upgrading his knowledge and credentials through seminars and courses.</P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="./gifs/pbfraser.gif" WIDTH=263 HEIGHT=239></CENTER>

<P>Allan believes that a personal concern for his clients, a strong commitment to service and the determination to provide the best advice he can, are the keys to his success.  He is married, with two teenage children, and lives in Nepean.  He has been involved with the study and practice of martial arts, particularly t'ai ch'i ch'uan, since his late teens.</P>
</TD></TR>
<TR><TD ALIGN=middle NOWRAP>
