<HEAD>
<TITLE>Greta N. Luimes in Detail...</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="./gifs/pbbckgnd.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>

<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=10>
<TR><TD ALIGN=middle>

<H2><I>Greta N. Luimes</I><BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="./gifs/greta.gif" ALT="Picture of Greta Luimes" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=200 HSPACE=0 ALIGN=top><BR><BR>
<I>Financial Planner</I><BR>
<H3><P>"Individuals in the '90's, whether young or old, are realizing their personal roles in preparing for their financial futures.  That may include an education, a new home, the retirement activities they dream about, or any other personal desire.  I am committed to enabling individuals and families to reach for their financial dreams, by building a disciplined and safe strategy together with them."
</TD><TD ROWSPAN=5 VALIGN=top>
<H3>
<P><IMG SRC="./gifs/pbicon2.gif" WIDTH=41 HEIGHT=33 ALIGN=baseline>After spending several years away from a medical technology career to raise her family, Greta embarked on a new path of interest.  Three years with a large accounting/consulting firm prepared her for the challenges of running this office and contributing to its growth.  She has served as our office manager and client service co-ordinator for the last two years.  Having a strong desire to teach our clients how they can achieve their long-term financial desires through the building of personal finance strategies, she moved into the role of financial planner.  Greta now plays an active role in the development and presentation of these solutions.</P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="./gifs/pbfraser.gif" WIDTH=263 HEIGHT=239></CENTER>

<P>Greta believes that a sincere and honest approach with clients will result in strong personal and business relationships.  She is married, has two teenage children and lives in Kanata.  She continues to participate in various leadership roles within her church and the private schools attended by her children.
</TD></TR>
