<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Memo from Peter B. Fraser to The Canadian Charter Banks</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>

<A HREF="./jan_p1.html"> <B><H1>... Thinking Outside the Box</B>
<BR><I>Issue #1 - January 1996</I></H1></A>
<H2>P. B. FRASER & ASSOCIATES<BR>
Financial Strategies Group</H2>
<HR SIZE=4>
<H1><I>Memo from Peter B. Fraser to The Canadian Charter Banks"</I>
<HR WIDTH=85% ALIGN=left SIZE=8 NOSHADE></H1>

<BR><P>January 12, 1996</P>


<CENTER>*************************MEMO***************************</CENTER>


<P>To: The Canadian Charter Banks</P>

<P>From: Peter B. Fraser</P>

<P>Please be aware that your introduction into the life insurance and "real world" mutual fund business has introduced the need for a great deal of responsibility on your parts.</P>

<P>Some of us in the financial planning profession welcome your acquisition of these products for two
reasons:</P>

<P>1. Canadians still append a significant degree of credibility to any product or strategy sanctioned by their banks. So your handling of life insurance and the most  widely recognized mutual funds will serve to
enhance the overall perception of these products. Thank you because that helps us, your competitor too.</P>

<P>2. Competition, that is, good, fair and balanced competition is wholesome and ultimately best for the
buying public. Your entry will not only keep us on our toes but striving to stay ahead of you in value and
performance.</P>

<P>I do caution you however not to assume that Canadians will line up for a dose of these products just
because you suddenly have them in your collection along with mortgages, car loans, lines of credit and
the like. Our experience is that people are really seeking a quality, compassion-filled relationship.</P>

<P>Life insurance and mutual funds are not bought over the counter after a 12 minute wait between the velvet railings. People who are serious and intent on learning to do better with what they have need more than the 2 - 3 minutes they can eke out of the transactional time allotted to them when the arrow goes on
pointing them to the next teller. They want a financial planner who will work FOR them, not do something
TO them.</P>

<P>Only a commitment to quality, servant-hearted relationships will do the trick here. Canadians will
participate vigorously when invited to do so and after having been thoroughly equipped and well taught.
So get your teaching cloaks on and be prepared.</P>

<P>I urge you to be credible, compassionate, self-less and laser-beam focussed on your customers' real
long-term needs, not only your banks' bottom line. As for us in the independent financial planning
segment, we'll see you at the finish line because we're in this for the long term.</P>

<HR SIZE=4>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=65%>
<TR><TD NOWRAP>
