<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Equal Access</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="ffffff" background="backgrounds/paper12l.jpg" TEXT="000000" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="000080" ALINK="0000FF">
<!-- *******************BEGIN EDITING HERE*************** -->
<IMG SRC="http://www2.ite.net/images/ite.gif" border=0 align=left>
<IMG SRC="images/extra.gif" border=0 align=right>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
To our friends, loyal IT&E customers, and other long-distance users:
<br><br>
Hafa Adai!
<br><br>
&#09;We at IT&E just wanted to let you know that there are a few changes in store for your off-island telephone dialing in 1997.  These changes, mandated by the Federal government, are designed to bring Guam into the North American Dialing Plan.  You will be hearing a lot of new terms over the next few months like <b><i>equal access, presubscription, and balloting</i></b>.  
So we thought you may want to learn what these words mean, and perhaps answer any other questions you may have as well.
<br><br>
&#09;For you, the telephone user, all the changes will basically boil down to one point:  you will need to select a "primary carrier" to use for all your long distance calls.
<br><br>
Confused?  That's okay.  IT&E has prepared this simple guide to answer frequently asked questions.  We hope that these Q&A's help to clarify things,
but if you have other questions, please call us at 646-8886.
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<h1>Frequently asked questions and answers:</h1>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>What will Equal Access mean to me?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Equal Access means that you will need to pick one "primary carrier" for all your direct-dialed, off-island telephone calls.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>What is a presubscription ballot?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Presubscription is your chance to "vote" for a preferred carrier.  GTA will soon be sending you a presubscription ballot to cast your vote.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When you receive the ballot, simply fill in the box next to IT&E and return the ballot as instructed.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or call IT&E at 646-8886.  One of our friendly cutomer service representatives will gladly assist you.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>Will this change how my phone works?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For the most part, no.  You will operate your phone exactly the same as before.  Dialing off-island, however, will be a little bit different.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Starting July 1, 1997, you will only need to dial "1" plus the area code and number on calls to all points.  To dial other countries, you will dial 011+country code+telephone number.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>When will I receive the presubscription ballot?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;GTA, through its agent NCS, will mail you a ballot at the end of March 1997.  You will have about 30 days to complete and return this ballot by mail.  For your convenience, you may return your ballot to any of IT&E's offices around the island.  We will also be happy to assist you in completing your ballot and answering any questions you may have.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>Is there anything that I have to do?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To make sure that you continue to receive IT&E's high quality service at our low rates, you should choose IT&E on your presubscription ballot.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>What if I fail to submit a ballot?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't worry.  A second ballot will be mailed out in May 1997, giving you a second chance to choose IT&E.  Or you can simply stop by an IT&E office or call us.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you fail to complete either ballot or consult with your IT&E agent,  GTA will randomly assign you a primary long distance carrier that may not meet your needs.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Therefore, it is very important that you make your choice and return the ballot on time.  If you wish, IT&E will be happy to assist you in completing and returning your ballot.  Simply drop by any of our IT&E offices or call us.
<br>
<br>
<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>Is there another way of making my selection?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, you may drop by IT&E's office and we will provide you with a <A HREF="loainfo.htm">Letter of Agency (LOA)</A>.  This LOA authorizes IT&E to act as an agent on your behalf
for the sole purpose of presubscribing your telephone number(s) to IT&E.
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or, you may also stop by GTA's business office and complete what's called a "super ballot."  For example, if you decide to use IT&E as your carrier, simply identify that in the ballot and sign it.
<br>
<br><FONT COLOR=0000A0>
<b>Why should I choose IT&E?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;IT&E has a solid reputation for superior quality, service, and value.  For example, by using IT&E you will:
<UL>
<LI>receive the lowest rates without sacrificing quality
<LI>receive the highest and most flexible discount calling plans
<LI>be connected to unlimited destinations worldwide
<LI>receive 24-hour operator service assistance
<LI>be offered the IT&E/AT&T Power Card which makes calling possible worldwide
<LI>be directly connected to AT&T, KDD Japan, PLDT Phillippines, as well as other major carriers
<LI>have access to IT&E's Internet, Video Conference, Switch 56, and many other value-added services
</UL>

<FONT COLOR=0000A0><b>If I select IT&E today, how can I be assured the greatest benefits?</b></FONT>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to providing the best service, only IT&E today gives you the lowest overall rates.  With a 
combination like that, you always win!
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the final analysis, our successful fourteen-year track record on Guam is your solid guarantee that you can get the 
biggest benefits only from IT&E, today and in the years to come.
<br>
<br>
<b><FONT COLOR=0000A0>So sign up today with IT&E, because...</FONT></b>
<br>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="images/bumpstick.gif" ALT="It pays to stay with IT&E" ALIGN="middle" BORDER=0>
</CENTER>
<br>
To register with IT&E click <a href="loa.htm">here</a>.
<hr>
<center>
<FONT COLOR=808080>Frequently Asked Questions</FONT> 
| <A HREF="loainfo.htm">Information about the Letter of Agency</A> 
| <A HREF="loa.htm">Letter of Agency</a>
| <A HREF="promotions.htm">Promotions</A>
</center>
<br>
<br>
