<A NAME="guide"></A><FONT=+4><STRONG>GUIDELINES FOR BILL PAYMENTS</STRONG></FONT>
<UL COMPACT>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">Financial institutions will only accept full payment as shown on the total due line of your statement.<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">If payment is made at a bank, then the statement stub will be retained by the bank; the banks validated statement will serve as your receipt.<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">Inquiries can be directed to any IT&E office.<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">Statements on past due accounts should be paid at an IT&E office to avoid possible service interruption.<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">Payments made before the end of the month will appear on your next billing statement.<BR>
<IMG SRC="images/greenb~1.gif">Payments are due on the 25th of the month in which billing was made.<BR>
<A HREF="#top"><center>(Back to top)</center></A>
</UL>

