</center>
<BR>
<A NAME="FIBER"><CENTER><STRONG><FONT SIZE=+1><EM>Fiber-Optic Networks</EM></FONT></STRONG></CENTER></A><BR>
<BR>
IT&E has made significant investments in the Fiber-Optic Network that spans the Pacific.  Communications traffic to and from Guam is routed primarily via fiber optic cables. With satellite circuits accommodating the overflow and with the completion of the Transpacific cable #5, IT&E is excited with it's investment into TPC5.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>TPC5</STRONG> is a self-healing system that is expected to answer an ever-growing demand for continued quality telecommunication service to Japan, Hawaii, the U.S. mainland, and ultimately connecting to the world. TPC5 has not only one,
but two pairs of cables.  The first, the Service Fiber Pair, is the main connection.  Should that system fail, traffic is automatically rerouted to the Restoration Fiber Pair, resulting in uninterruptable service.  The PacRim West cable network is the first direct connection from Guam to Australia and the South Pacific. In years past, telecommunications to Australia were connected through a U.S. mainland route.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="SDI"><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG><EM>Switch Digital International Service (IT&E/AT&T)</EM></CENTER></STRONG></FONT></A><BR>
<BR>
<center>
<table width=90% align=center>
<td><center><IMG hspace=10 SRC="images/sdiguy.jpg"></center>
</td>
<td>
<STRONG>SDI</STRONG> is a high speed, 56KB alternative to international private lines. It is the first fully digital, dial up 56 Kbps service from Guam to the U.S. and international locations and is the first service to use the international achitecture, including CCITT #7 Signaling Protocol.  SDI is the international extension of the domestic AT&T Accunet Switched Digital Service.  Available on demand with usage-sensitive pricing, SDI can be used to facilitate the following applications:<BR>
<BR>
</td> 
<tr>
</table></center>
<UL COMPACT>
<IMG HSPACE=2 SRC="images/blueball.gif"><STRONG>VideoConferencing</STRONG>: Face to face videoconferencing allows moving ideas instead of people. It is an intelligent, hard working alternative to international travel.<BR>
<BR>
<IMG HSPACE=2 SRC="images/blueball.gif"><STRONG>Group IV Facsimile</STRONG>:  High resolution facsimile transmits a page of printed material in less than 10 seconds with photocopy quality.  Its a bigger step forward from earlier technology which required as much as 60 seconds a page for international transmission.<BR>
<BR>
<IMG HSPACE=2 SRC="images/blueball.gif"><STRONG>Electronic Date Transfer</STRONG>: Move large amounts of data between computers separated by oceans, virtually the same speed achieved between offices today. SDI establishes circuits on demand.  Pay only for the duration of data transfer for inventory records, payroll logs, database updates, remote job entry, and distribute data processing.<BR>
<BR>
<IMG HSPACE=2 SRC="images/blueball.gif"><STRONG>Dial Back Up</STRONG>: SDI provides essential protection in the event of network failure. Use the service to quickly dial up the isolated locations and re-establish connectivity for data and video traffic.<BR>
<BR>
<IMG HSPACE=2 SRC="images/blueball.gif"><STRONG>CAD/CAM transmission</STRONG>: Give internationally distributed workstations real-time access to remote databases and powerful central computers.  SDI convenience and reliability can keep the critical design process moving forward at top speed.
</UL>
<A NAME="LEASELINE"><EM><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Private Lease Lines</FONT></STRONG></A></EM></CENTER><BR>
Provided as a dedicated communication link between Guam and the Continental U.S. or Guam and designated countries, private lines allow unlimited use of facilities with the convenience of a fixed monthly cost.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="BOOTHS"><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG><EM>Long Distance Calling Booths</A> and <A HREF="ite_bill.htm">Billing Locations</FONT></STRONG></EM></A></CENTER><BR>
Located throughout Guam, IT&Es Long Distance calling booths are readily available for those customers without telephones in their residences or place of business.<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1><CENTER><A NAME="GTA"><EM><STRONG>IT&E/(GTA) Liaison Service</STRONG></EM></FONT></A>
</CENTER>
Customer service is a top priority for IT&E. Our company has come up with a gem of a plan to assist customers with their requests for installations and new lines. A liaison service is currently set up between IT&E and the Guam Telephone Authority (GTA).  Instead of running around and tackling the task of  requesting service directly with GTA, all  a customer has to do is notify an IT&E Account Executive, who will gladly do the leg work for you. For more information, call our Liaison at 649-4483.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="MAINTENANCE"><CENTER><EM><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Maintenance Support</CENTER></STRONG></EM></FONT></A><BR>
Where there is a product, there should also be a mechanism installed for the maintenance of that particular item.Thats why IT&E has set up a 24- hour dispatch center for the maintenance of its products. The center provides on-call factory trained technicians to install and/or maintain PABX, Key Systems, Integrated Call Accounting Systems, and other interfaces to meet all your telecommunication requirements. For more information on Maintenance Support, please call 646-9317.<BR>
