<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Residential Products and Services: Long Distance Calling Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="images/bsoup050.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#00006F" VLINK="#000000" ALINK="#600000">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3>Long Distance Calling Programs</FONT></CENTER>

<HR WIDTH=80% ALIGN=center SIZE=5>

<FONT SIZE=+1><CENTER><A NAME="right"><IMG SRC="images/right1.gif" ALT="[The Right Plan]"></A></CENTER></FONT>
<center><table><td width=50 border=0></td><td>
True to its reputation for being Guam's telecommunications leader, IT&E once again charges forward first and introduces new,
reduced long distance rates.
<br>
<br>
Effective March 1, 1997, Guam's only locally-owned, full-service long distance telecommunications company introduces the 
<i>new</i> Right Plan, complete with across-the-board savings for all direct dial long distance calling all week long, on all
numbers you call, all the time and to all locations.
<br>
<br>
Plus, calling long distance with IT&E is now just a matter of seconds, so to speak, in that rates are based on six second increments.
That means you're only charged for the time you actually spend on line.
<br>
<br>
For callers to the U.S., there's more good news.  The <i>new</i> Right Plan has absorbed IT&E's Discover America rates to the fifty states - 
allowing a continuance of a 20 cents per minute rate everyday from 5 p.m. to 5 a.m. and all weekend long from 5 p.m. Friday to 5 a.m. Monday.
<br>
<br>
The <i>new</i> Right Plan rates are available at the customer service counters at any IT&E sattelite office and at the IT&E main office
in Tamuning.<BR></td></table></center>


<br>
<br>

