<HTML><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<img src=/methodist/icon/H-RSRC.GIF>
<h1><hr size=6><font size=+3>
<b>Additional Health Resources</b></font><hr size=6></h1>
</center></font>

<B>AGING</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.mbnet.mb.ca/crm/other/postl1.html>
E-mail Resources on Aging</a>
<br>Links to various sites on aging.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>ALZHEIMER'S</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.alz.org/>Alzheimer's Association</A>
<BR>What Alzheimer's Disease is and isn't; caregiver resources; medical information
and links to other Alzheimer's-related sites.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>ARTHRITIS</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.Arthritis.org/>Arthritis Foundation</A>
<BR> Facts about arthritis, FAQs, news
</UL>
<HR>

<B>AUDIOLOGY</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.sconcept.com/hearing.htm>Hearing Exchange Online</A>
<BR>Offers lots of links to hearing health information resources and special interest
forums on a variety of topics related to hearing.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>CANCER</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.nci.nih.gov/>The National Cancer Institute</A>
<BR> Lots of cancer information, including CancerNet. Huge resource for health care
professionals and patients.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://www.cancer.org/acs.html>American Cancer Society</A>
<BR>Cancer information and ACS programs.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>DIABETES AND KIDNEY DISEASE</B><UL>
<A HREF= http://www.diabetes.org/>American Diabetes Association</A>
<BR>Information about diabetes, its treatment, how to live with it and possible 
complications and concerns.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://www.adatx.org/>Texas Affiliate of the American Diabetes Association</A>
<BR>Offers a Texas Resource Directory, a Physicians' Online Forum, books available
through the ADA, info on scientific research and rnore.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://www.niddk.nih.gov/>National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Disease</A>
<BR>Information on diabetes, digestive diseases, endocrine disorders, hematologic
disorders, kidney disorders, nutrition and obesity and urologic disorders.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>EYE DISEASE</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.eyenet.org/>American Academy of Ophthalmology</A>
<BR>All about the eye-anatomy, diseases and conditions, FAQs, facts and myths, 
latest advances.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>GENERAL HEALTH</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.cdc.gov/>Centers for Disease Control</A>
<BR>Information on diseases, health risks and prevention, as well as health advice for
those planning an international trip. Lots of national statistics and studies on
health tends.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://galaxy.einet.net/galaxy/Medicine.html>EINet Galaxy - Medicine</A>
<BR>Tons of medical links.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://nhic-nt.health.org/>National Health Information,Center</A>
<BR>From a division of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, links to
federal health information and a keyword data base search.
<BR>
<A HREF=http://www.library.tmc.edu/> Houston Academy of Medicine - Texas Medical Center Library</A>
<BR>Gateway to a massive medical library
</UL>
<HR>

<B>HEART DISEASE</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.amhrt.org/>American Heart Association</A>
<BR>Information on cardiovascular diseases and stroke, heart disease prevention and
support groups.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>NEUROLOGY</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.lm.com:80/~nab/> Neurosciences on the Internet</A>
<BR>Extensive list of online information.
</UL>
<HR>

<B>SURGERY</B><UL>
<A HREF=http://www.bcm.tmc.edu/surgery/> Baylor Department of Surgery </A>
<BR>Information about services and faculty at Baylor College of Medicine's Department of Surgery.
</UL>
   
